<userid>113007033156746127577<//userid>< user_name>
Chase<//user_name>
<date>1561005358535< /date><Rating>1</Rating>< Review>
I set up my membership at Equinox Beverly Hills location at the end of April for it to be set up for the first of May. My first issue happened when I went to use my 15% first purchase in the store. I went in right after a class on May 20th and was looking at a couple items. The lady who was helping me was very nice and grabbed everything I needed and told me that if I don't want to try anything on just to buy it and bring it home and bring it back within 30 days for a refund.

When i got home to try on a pair of shorts I looked at the receipt and saw that it said in store exchange only. I called first thing on May 21st and asked to talk to the store manager. I spoke to Ari (assistant store manager) who told me to call back and ask for Erica (the store manager) about what can be done.

When I called back to talk to Erica she once again told me there was nothing that could be done. I told her that although the women who helped me the day before was very helpful, the policy was not told to me otherwise I would not have purchased the items and brought them home to try. She once again told me that there was nothing that she could do and "The register wouldn't let her refund me even if she wanted to" I then asked if there was someone else in the building that I could talk to that may be able to help me. She then said "When you call with something about the store, I'm who you get" and then hung up the phone.

I then proceeded to find a customer service number online and email address. memadmin@equinox.com.I have now reached out to them 7 times and have also called 14 times trying to get ahold of someone that could help and also reach out to the Beverly Hills Branch.After no response was made from the corporate customer care, I then proceeded to file 5 reports with the gym itself. I finally was able to get ahold of someone who was very helpful by the name of Corbin (Corporate Customer Care) on June 5th who apologized for everything and told me that he would reach out directly to the District Shop Manager, Pooneh Naerzare.

On June 12th I finally received an email from Pooneh apologizing for me recent experience in the store and told me that she would gladly issue me a refund and make sure that I am taken care of and when I will be able to go into the store. I wrote back the June 13th telling her that I would be able to go in that same day or the next, whichever works best for her. I have still to hear a response.

On June 19th I finally decided to go in and ask to speak to a gym manager about the refund. I went to the front desk while a gentleman checked me in and ask what the issue was about. After explaining the issues that I have had he asked me to take a seat and Don would be over as soon as he was able to talk. Don came about 15 minutes later and asked me to come to his office. I told him about the issue with the shorts and showed him the email from Pooneh (THE DISTRICT STORE MANAGER) and he told me that he would only give me in store credit for the item and that she did not state that the refund would be made back onto my credit card.

I told him that I would then like to just cancel my membership because I would no longer like to be a member at a gym that has zero customer care. He then told me that I signed a 1 year contract and there was nothing that I could do. I then told him about the messages that I had between the membership specialist Saul and I, where he clearly told me "exactly right, just let me know and I can cancel it anytime." Don then told me "Well that just looks like part of the conversation and not the whole conversation" which is when I left.

I have had issue after issue since I signed up for this gym membership with a bunch of managers who "have nothing that they can do" when you are finally able to get a hold of one. I just wanted everyone to know about these issues because if you sign up for a membership here be prepared to be took, ignored, taken advantage of, and be offered zero customer service.<//Review>

<user_id>104873715084082750977< /user_id><Name>Garrett Thierry<//Name>< date>
1535144186789< /date>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< text>
If your lifestyle is centered around Fitness and Health, the Equinox has everything one needs to learn, grow, improve, or maintain health and athletic performance.  The class offerings are wide and diverse, whether you are a beginner to fitness, or looking to add spice up your current exercise regimen, Equinox has the classes you need.  Tabata, Yoga, Pilates, Dance, and a myriad of other course offerings staffed with incredibly passionate and engaging instructors.  The Yoga Program at Equinox was a major plus for me, offering Iyengar, Vinyasa, and Yin, all of which are necessary components to a well rounded mind and body exercise program.  The biggest obstacle to Equinox is parking, the two hour time limit pressures one to quickly be in and out of the facility. The Cafe inside the Equinox in Beverly Hills is fantastic, really unique and tasty smoothies, as well as pre-workout blends to energize, fuel, and refuel after rigorous workouts.  As for the Equinox facility, the locker rooms are incredibly clean and well maintained by a friendly staff that is always responsive and helpful with any issues or concerns with lockers or towels.  The Shampoos and Conditioners are Organic and there are free razors and shaving cream to use as a perk to ones membership package.  The membership levels range in price, however If you have a traveling lifestyle the Global Executive membership is worth the investment, providing access to all Equinox locations.

Equinox should really thank me, 3 people now signed.  Reminiscing about the year spent bouncing around the #equinox gyms in Southern California. I hear they have a global pass. #committosomething<//text>

< review>
ATTENTION TO ALL EQUINOX MEMBERS!!!! THE GYM HAS THIEFS WORKING FOR THEM
I have been a member of Equinox since the moment they opened a new location in BEVERLY HILLS 7 years ago . about 10 days ago I checked in at 5pm and after working out I found my locker busted open with some sort of cobra or tools. They STOLE my entire bag with a Rolex watch wallet and car keys . I called the manager and he suggested to make a police report but did not call the police there. He said not to worry he will take care of me and tried to calmed me down . I am sure he was trying to protect the image that this gym has to show to their clients .I personally expressed my concerns about this been an inside job and I was sure the bag was still there somewhere .I asked him to check the camera videos to see if the bag (very big bag)made it out of the gym. At night he called me and told he personally checked every locker and went around the gym and the bag was not there . So I filed a police report , I asked the police if the gym was supposed to call them and the officer said that it was up to them but yes they should had call them because this was a crime with damage inside their property .About five days after the incident the manager called me again and told me they found the bag . I asked him where and he said inside a different locker . I realized immediately that I was right ,this was an inside job and they put the bag back in the a different locker after hiding it somewhere where regular member don t have access .No member or daily guest would had risked to bring that bag back inside the gym .Of course my watch and cash were gone . The Gym does not carry any sort of insurance and they claim to not be responsible for any of this actions happening in their facilities . I mentioned to them one thing is to find the locker open maybe because you forgot it open or because someone found your digital combination but it is different finding it busted open in a gym like that where they charge us so much money . I was told they did not want to take any responsibility and they offered only 3 months of free membership .I told them I was aware I could not get back 10k for my watch but I was at least expecting a better treatment also because they know it is an internal problem going on lately . It took almost a week to get in touch with regional manager and the Vice president and I was told the same exact thing . I explained I have been a member for long time and I had at least 10 people joining that gym because my referral ,but still they did not care . When I said I will report this on every site and I will talk to every member in the gym the regional manager answered he will have to suspend my membership if I acted that way . In other words they want you to work out with all your belonging including your car keys , i.d. and credit cards in your pocket because they don t have a better system to give you any protection. they want high end clientele to join their gym but don`t protect you on this matters and they don t want this news to spread . They have an internal investigation going on but they won`t show me the videos or let me speak with their investigator for sharing info. Very horrible way to handle this and I am sure many clients will judge them .<//review>

< Review>
I visited for the first time yesterday and I could not be more happy with my experience. After 12 years of going to the same stylist, I had to find a new one and Rob helped put me at ease that I was in good hands.  He asked me all the right questions so he could match me with the right stylist. It can be really difficult and overwhelming to figure out how to find a new hair stylist, right?

My appointment was with Jessica Sager, and from the moment I sat in her chair I felt completely comfortable. Our first appointment included plenty of intro time to discuss my hair and the kind of color and services she thought would be best for me. She immediately put me at ease given that she knew I was nervous about trying a brand new stylist after such a long time.

I have to say that working with her was the best thing I have done for my hair in years. I was expecting her work to be good, but actually my hair and color came out better than I could have imagined. I'm a blonde, and her ideas and suggestions for how she wanted to highlight and add base color were incredible. <Review>I recently spent 4 days over NY at JMH and three additional outpatient visits relating to a liver obstruction.  I found the experience including personnel, information, and procedures shockingly poor in several instances.  On NY eve they attempted a procedure which didn't work, but they could not perform the alternative procedure the next day because all of the Drs were let off for NY Day.   but they would not let me leave so I spent NY eve and NY day in the hospital with no care, information or anything to do when I could have gone home. the following day I had the alternative procedure.  the dr only spoke to me just before and after the procedure.  no checkups, visits, calls or details.  the nurses could not answer a single question I asked about what was happening. I was told to continue the alternative treatment for "one to two weeks" and then make an outpatient appt to reverse part of the procedure.  while being discharged they put all my clothes and belongings in a plastic bag and had me sign a form I had received my belongings.  when I got home, I realised my medications which they had taken away and stored in their pharmacy, were not with my belongings.  I called to tell them and asked if they would send someone to return them since it was their error.  A very surly nurse snapped "you signed the form saying you got your belongings didn't you?"  so it was all my fault and I had to drive back to the hospital to pick them up.    I asked the nurse what was the difference between one and two weeks clinically as I wanted to get it done asap.  she told me it had to do with when the drainage stopped from the external drain.  This proved to be completely false, as normal drainage would continue indefinitely. it turned out the "one to two weeks" had more to do with the dr schedule and being away for a conference, so it was scheduled for more than two weeks later. I arrived for that appt where the procedure was internalised and the drainage bag removed but the line left in and capped off. I was told this was because I needed a week's script of vit K to normalize my clotting factors.then to go to the lab for a vit K value and make an appt to have the external line removed.   The report they gave me of the procedure and followup correctly described the procedure and the vit K regimen, but the follow up read "make appt at Drs office in 2-3 weeks to discuss biopsy results".  This was totally someone else's followup lifted to my report not mine. there was no biopsy or appt at dr office.  it should have read "make out patient appt to remove external line". I found that to be a shocking error, but I did make the appt and called to ask if I would be under anaesthesia and was told yes.  so I was in the OR being prepped, with 4 nurses who couldn't decide if I was to be on my side or my back ,and then I asked again about the anaesthesia and one nurse said "oh no, no anaesthesia; he will just pull the line out".  another nurse said "I think he is going to do an endoscopy which would require anaesthesia". the four argued back and forth as I'm lying there for the procedure and they didn't 'even know what was being done.  they finally went to find the dr who said yes it would be anaesthesia. I finally had the procedure and left after recovery.  The reason I called ahead about the anaesthesia was that they require a driver to pick you up and I said I really didn't have anyone so what happens if I don't have a driver. This is not to say all of the nurses were unpleasant; some were very nice, or that the dr didnt' perform admirably; it's just that they never checked in on me or explained things. <UserId.>109744811928433206378< /UserId.>< resp>
None<//resp>
<review>11/30/14

I've been in the cardiovascular building at John Muir many times for different reasons, most recently, last night (Saturday). On the way into the building there are face masks and hand sanitizer.  Inside, my husband and I stopped in the lobby to look at the prettily decorated Christmas tree and other decorations. The main front desk was empty but we were able to find a directional guide near the elevator and figure out which floor we needed.

The second floor is home to the progressive care unit - where a patient may be moved after ER, but before a surgery.  There is a large waiting room with a TV and many chairs, so your family and friends can come see you but not all crowd your private room at once.  Outside of that waiting room is a front desk where I found two friendly girls sitting - happy to direct me to the room I was looking for.

Many of the private rooms are very spacious - the one I saw last night had 6 people comfortable sitting in it - and only one patient.  He had a private bathroom and it was set up very nicely. It's nice to know that your loved one is really being cared for.  Outside of this patient's room there was another desk with three other staff people working and checking on patients.  Everything was very clean (duh, it's a hospital).

I really have only had good experiences here when talking with staff and patients. <review>On 3/23/2018 around midnight I had severe chest pains that led me to John Muir ER in Concord. There was no one there and I was admitted right away! She gave me two and my blood pressure plummeted into the 70's, I thought I was going to die!! many nurses came in and were shocked along with the Dr. when she came in. I was so scared! I then was admitted. I really wanted to leave but was so incredibly weak. I didn't want to, it was humiliating. She said it was policy and all hospitals do this! She made me feel if I didn't I was hiding something. I was told I would have a stress test between 8 am and 9:30 am, the nurse comes in and says it won't be till 2:30 or 3 pm. I didn't want to stay, at this time my blood work came back fine. At 10:30 I had not eaten and was starved, I was told conflicting stories that I had to fast, others saying I could eat. My nurse said she would get me breakfast at around 10:30 am. I get on the treadmill, I do quite well for being exhausted and still having chest pain and with no pain reliever and put through hell! She then puts full speed and I can't do it anymore! The cardiologist comes in and says I'm too young not to finish and berates me. Then they start talking about me with the Dr.'s back to me. My husband speaks up against their behavior. To sum up my experience here: I would recommend no one ever coming here! I have never been so scared, humiliated, violated! They are criminal and I hope they close this hell hole! Darius X<//username>
<Time>1485206723987</Time>< rating>
4<//rating>
< review>
This location was recently remodeled which included a major expansion of the pumping stations (from 8 to 16 pumps). This was for   the anticipation of the much higher vehicle traffic from the new four lane expansion of highway 76.

Since the facility was originally planned for lighter use, the new tramac had to be squeezed into a small space. As a result, entry and exit can get very tricky with cars backing out, pulling in and turning in tight spots.

There are no restroom facilities in the Arco itself but there is a McDonald's connected where you can walk right through from the store. It is one of the newer McCafe's with a warmer, upscale dining area that has available wifi.

The staff is always very friendly and personable from my many trips here (even gave out free cookies :).</review>

None</pics>

< user_id>
116528117830833143869</user_id>
< username>
Celestial Cat<//username>
<date>1534489454308<//date><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
I have rented storage space from a handful of companies over the years. Most places are all about the same . . . modest to modern offices, and rental spaces that consist of a metal door and ceiling, and three walls of drywall, decorated with plywood patches covering damaged drywall. They all charge close to the same rates for about the same services.

So I was skeptical when my realtor highly recommended US Storage on Foster Road in Norwalk, just because she had nothing but the highest praise for this location, where she stores her own personal stuff. If it weren't for the fact that she is also a dear friend, I would have suspected she was recommending it for a kickback.

The rent for the Public Storage room I had was going up 20% after only three months, despite the fact they had NOT indicated what I'd been paying was an introductory rate. So I knew I had to get out of there fast, and researched my friend's recommendation of US Storage online, and arranged to go in to rent a unit. I expected to see what I've always seen at storage places, so I was absolutely floored when I got there, and saw that it was everything my friend had said . . .

First impression was amazing! This place is huge, with the buildings facing the street decorated to look like pleasant housing or office parks so it doesn't look like an unsightly industrial block to mar the look of the neighborhood. Their office is modern and pleasant, and I was immediately greeted by the managers, Yvette and Filbert, who were very friendly, efficient, accommodating and informative. They did everything they could to make the transition easier, including the FREE use of their moving truck for the day!

Filbert took me out to the unit in a golf cart, and I could see their location is huge! Over 1,000 units! The area was neat and clean, and solar panels provide their electricity needs. Everything about the place told me it was well~planned and executed, corporate~run, not a franchise, and everything run to corporate standards!

THE BEST PART was seeing the unit itself! No pockmarked drywall with plywood decor! Wall to wall, floor to ceiling was clean corrugated metal walls, to keep the contents safe from being pilfered through through units! I loved that the units have ALARMS with a clever means of activation, and the doors have a locking system like nothing I've seen before, absolutely unbreakable. The unit looked brand new and well~sealed against pests.

All of this, and their prices are absolutely competitive with other companies! Now I understand my friend's excitement! Just like I was floored by my friend's recommendation, which seemed just impossible or at the very least, very exaggerated, now YOU're reading MY review and probably thinking the same thing. I assure you, prior to my friend's recommendation, I'd had NO knowledge of or affiliation with US Storage ~ Foster, and there is no monetary benefit for writing this review. I just wish I'd found them years ago, if there is anything I can do to send customers their way, AND also help YOU by recommending a great storage facility, I'm happy to do it! Life has enough complications, more things in life need to be this easy and worry~free!

:-) Have a lovely day!</review>
